Year 2020 was marked by the locust invasion, floods and drought, and a staggering economy, helped into the abyss by Covid-19 devastation.We are staring at a Sh8.4 trillion debt against a ceiling of Sh9 trillion. It may sound insincere to send you the traditional Happy New Year goodwill message against the backdrop of the times we live in, our bitter experience this year, and an uncertain 2021.
However, it’s in times of gloom like we live in now that the true character of a Kenyan is manifested. Kenyans are generally warm, optimistic and resilient people. I cannot take it past them that they are looking at 2020 as a memory and 2021 with hope. This is the spirit that has seen Kenyans overcome untold misery meted on them by nature and inconsiderate governments.



