We cannot, therefore, wipe away the Christmas smile and New Year cheer from Kenyan faces even under the torrid conditions of ravaging Covid-19 and real destitution. Year 2020 was marked by the locust invasion, floods and drought, and a staggering economy, helped into the abyss by Covid-19 devastation. It’s not easy to recount the personal anguish of Kenyans, without feeling guilty; as leaders, we did nothing meaningful to halt and arrest the hurt.



