Civid-19 did not cause our economic decay, but only accelerated it. The warnings we were digging the wrong hole economically were always there. We went into a borrowing binge that upset our dwindling balance of payments. But the more dangerous the debt exposure we run into, the more borrowing we signed onto until the troubles we face today exploded.
Structural Adjustment Programmes
We are staring at a Sh8.4 trillion debt against a ceiling of Sh9 trillion. The country is on the chopping block of bankruptcy because we borrowed expensive commercial loans with high yielding interest in a very short time. With corruption skimming its share, we invested in flashy projects without guaranteed immediate returns. Worse would come when loans investment was not yielding returns to pay back.



